When the come back is STRONG. 
.
Fun fact:
I took nearly two years off all gym activity. 
Started working with @gradyreily back in November to help me get back into shape for my birthday and help me remember why I love lifting heavy shit! (Y’all I was a total mess) It worked! He’s an excellent bodybuilding/nutrition coach if you’re looking for help! 
After my Birthday I decided I wanted to get back into my true passion- powerlifting!
Been working with @tyler_tir for the past 4 weeks and couldn’t be happier with the progress! I FEEL STRONG AF ! I love this shit! 
.
Though I admire bodybuilding for the discipline and strategy involved, it just wasn’t the sport for me. I don’t have the genetics for it. 
At some point, if you’re smart, you’ll embrace your talents- even if they don’t always match up with your initial dreams. 
IM BUILT FOR POWERLIFTING.

5 month old Brangus steer

To be honest, I never expected to like cows as much as I do. Fascinated by the whole process of hand raised beef. Researching the different feeding strategies (and TRUST ME every single person you ask does something different) - there are so many unique and highly strategic techniques to, not only maximize the quality of the beef produced, but also the quality of life for the animal. 
HAPPY COWS TASTE BETTER 🙌🏼❤️❤️ 
.
.
This is Penny. 1.5years old ANGUS heifer. 
She was orphaned as a baby. I bottle fed her and now she’s like a giant happy puppy. She will be bred next year and I’m excited to see and learn through that whole process.

The amount of channeled aggression the flows through this place gives me great PEACE. 
.
.
AGGRESSIVELY HAPPY
